    "headline": "Global Bond Rout Eases as Oil Spurs Trader Rethink on Rates",
    "summary": "While short-dated US Treasuries remained slightly lower on the session, those maturing in seven years or more were little changed as of midday in New York as the overnight oil shock abated.  Global bonds were hit hard as the trading week began with a surge in oil toward $120 a barrel prompted investors to price in higher inflation despite risk to the economic growth outlook.  The yield on benchmark 10-year US Treasuries were back to 4.13% after spiking to 4.21%, while the rate on policy-sensitive two-year notes remained two basis points higher at 3.58%.",
