    "headline": "US Bonds Rise as Trump Hint at Ending War Eases Inflation Angst",
    "summary": "Trump’s comments on Monday afternoon sent oil back below $90 a barrel, easing concerns that rising energy prices would fuel inflation.  Yields on 10-year Treasuries were ending the session lower by four basis points at around 4.09% after earlier spiking to 4.21%.  “The markets have done some talking here via the higher oil price, elevated volatility,” higher yields and risk-off sentiment that’s threatening to get worse, said Padhraic Garvey, head of research for the Americas at ING.",
